{
  "description": "GTA (General Terms of Agreement) maximum daily settlement rates for credit hire vehicles. Rates are excluding VAT.",
  "notes": [
    "All daily settlement rates are excluding VAT.",
    "An additional \u00a35 per day can be added for automatics (where this matches the customer's vehicle) unless the model listed is already an automatic.",
    "Vehicles with semi-shift/direct shift gearboxes (e.g. paddle shift) that can change gears manually or automatically qualify for the \u00a35 per day automatic uplift.",
    "An additional \u00a35 per day can be added for estate vehicles (where this matches the customer's vehicle) unless the model listed is already an estate.",
    "An additional \u00a35 per day can be added for necessary extras such as tow bars and baby seats which reflect the customer's damaged vehicle type/fitments.",
    "An additional \u00a312 per day add-on for dual control vehicles (\u00a37 per day if insurance cover not provided).",
    "For convertibles not already listed as convertibles, place them into the group higher than the hard top version (e.g. BMW M3 is SP9, convertible equivalent is SP10).",
    "Disabled driver vehicles: reasonable direct costs plus \u00a310 administration charge. Special adaptations should be discussed with insurer at time hire commences.",
    "No charge for additional drivers unless non-standard risk. Non-standard risk examples: under 25 or over 70, held full licence less than 12 months, certain occupations, convictions resulting in unspent ban or 7+ points.",
    "Where no appropriate group exists for a commercial vehicle (e.g. hearse, refrigerated vehicle, car transporter) the CHO is advised to try and agree a rate with the insurer before the commencement of the hire to eliminate later disputes over rates.",
    "Motorcycles: £35 plus VAT allowed for motorcycle topboxes/panniers where the customer can demonstrate a need and regular use.",
    "Private Hire & Taxi: Each group has two rates — one for newer vehicles (under 3 or 4 years old) and one for aged vehicles (3+ or 4+ years old). No additions allowed for signage, radio hire, or taxi display equipment, but actual Council costs for replating vehicles and fitting different radio are reimbursable at cost."
  ],
